article.headline: Weber St. 61, N. Colorado 60
article.story: GREELEY, Colo. (AP) -- Kirk Archibeque's shot was wide right as time expired as Weber State beat Northern Colorado 61-60 Thursday night. David Patten scored 21 points for Weber State (8-6) and handed Northern Colorado (2-11) a loss in its inaugural Big Sky Conference game. Bears coach Tad Boyle wanted a foul called on Archibeque's rebound of a Sean Taibi and missed shot but got none. Archibeque led UNC with 18 points, while Dwayne Birden added 17. Northern Colorado missed all 12 of their 3-point shots while Weber State was 7-of-21 from beyond the arc.
